text: Thliptoceras artatalis is a moth in the family Crambidae. It was described by Aristide Caradja in 1925. It is found in southern China in Zhejiang, Fujian, Jiangxi, Guangdong, Guangxi, Hainan and Guizhou. The wingspan is 22–28 mm. The wings are yellow with a contrasting brown termen. ==References== Category:Moths described in 1925 Category:Pyraustinae
title: Thliptoceras artatalis
